00:44:57.950 --> 00:45:01.490 align:middle line:90%
to becoming very emotional.

00:45:01.490 --> 00:45:05.870 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, we also
recognize that to feel deeply

00:45:05.870 --> 00:45:09.800 align:middle line:84%
is an initiation into
living more fully.

00:45:09.800 --> 00:45:12.120 align:middle line:90%
So we get these things mixed up.

00:45:12.120 --> 00:45:16.900 align:middle line:84%
The difference between
feeling and becoming emotional

00:45:16.900 --> 00:45:19.870 align:middle line:90%
is the attachment of a story.

00:45:19.870 --> 00:45:24.500 align:middle line:84%
The need to know why
I'm having this feeling.

00:45:24.500 --> 00:45:27.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NARRATOR: One day in Bali,
I made a trip with friends

00:45:27.180 --> 00:45:29.100 align:middle line:90%
to a waterfall.

00:45:29.100 --> 00:45:34.280 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, my seven-year-old
son, Moritz, was gone.

00:45:34.280 --> 00:45:39.250 align:middle line:84%
For two hours I desperately
searched him in a rainy jungle,

00:45:39.250 --> 00:45:41.570 align:middle line:84%
finally, he came back
with two of my friends

00:45:41.570 --> 00:45:43.510 align:middle line:84%
who didn't tell me
that they would walk

00:45:43.510 --> 00:45:46.420 align:middle line:90%
with him to another waterfall.

00:45:46.420 --> 00:45:50.900 align:middle line:84%
Even now that he was back, I
felt anger towards my friends

00:45:50.900 --> 00:45:55.190 align:middle line:84%
and remembered an advice that
Arjuna Ardagh had given me.

00:45:55.190 --> 00:45:57.380 align:middle line:84%
>>When you feel
angry, see if it's

00:45:57.380 --> 00:46:00.927 align:middle line:84%
possible to feel the anger,
even to express the anger

00:46:00.927 --> 00:46:02.915 align:middle line:90%
for a couple of minutes.

00:46:02.915 --> 00:46:06.090 align:middle line:90%
[YELLING]

00:46:06.090 --> 00:46:09.240 align:middle line:84%
>>Oh, I feel so
angry I could kill.

00:46:09.240 --> 00:46:09.740 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:46:09.740 --> 00:46:10.840 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong?

00:46:10.840 --> 00:46:11.630 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:46:11.630 --> 00:46:13.570 align:middle line:84%
I just feel this way
and it feels good.

00:46:13.570 --> 00:46:16.895 align:middle line:90%


00:46:16.895 --> 00:46:17.750 align:middle line:90%
This is liberating.

00:46:17.750 --> 00:46:20.590 align:middle line:84%
If you enter into anger
without any story,

00:46:20.590 --> 00:46:22.870 align:middle line:90%
the anger becomes power.

00:46:22.870 --> 00:46:27.520 align:middle line:84%
The power becomes your
original nature, which is love.

00:46:27.520 --> 00:46:30.030 align:middle line:84%
If you enter into
anger with a story,

00:46:30.030 --> 00:46:31.880 align:middle line:90%
it's focused on something else.

00:46:31.880 --> 00:46:33.150 align:middle line:90%
Now there's blame.

00:46:33.150 --> 00:46:33.800 align:middle line:90%
You did this.

00:46:33.800 --> 00:46:34.800 align:middle line:90%
This is why I feel this.

00:46:34.800 --> 00:46:35.990 align:middle line:90%
And you made me feel.

00:46:35.990 --> 00:46:39.090 align:middle line:84%
And you enter into
an endless realm

00:46:39.090 --> 00:46:41.100 align:middle line:90%
now of action and response.

00:46:41.100 --> 00:46:43.220 align:middle line:84%
And so it goes on,
and on, and on.

00:46:43.220 --> 00:46:47.290 align:middle line:84%
Becoming emotional
will wrap you up more

00:46:47.290 --> 00:46:51.150 align:middle line:84%
in the traps of
the thinking mind.

00:46:51.150 --> 00:46:56.220 align:middle line:84%
Feeling deeply will bring
you home to yourself.

00:46:56.220 --> 00:46:59.870 align:middle line:84%
Your feelings become
a teacher, a guide,

00:46:59.870 --> 00:47:04.740 align:middle line:84%
when you can follow
them free of thought.

00:47:04.740 --> 00:47:09.240 align:middle line:84%
>>NARRATOR: Emotions, a
powerful source of energy

00:47:09.240 --> 00:47:15.450 align:middle line:84%
if I avoid to blame others and
to attach personal stories.

00:47:15.450 --> 00:47:19.272 align:middle line:90%
But what if I still do?

00:47:19.272 --> 00:47:22.540 align:middle line:90%
[INTENSE MUSIC]

00:47:22.540 --> 00:47:25.080 align:middle line:84%
>>Many of us hold the
grievances, the hurts

00:47:25.080 --> 00:47:27.336 align:middle line:84%
that we've had, inside
for generations.

00:47:27.336 --> 00:47:29.614 align:middle line:84%
Look at the wars that are
going on in the world.

00:47:29.614 --> 00:47:31.030 align:middle line:84%
People fighting
against each other

00:47:31.030 --> 00:47:34.600 align:middle line:84%
because they hold anger
towards each other.

00:47:34.600 --> 00:47:36.320 align:middle line:10%
I think one of the
most important tools

00:47:36.320 --> 00:47:38.840 align:middle line:10%
that we can develop
as human beings,

00:47:38.840 --> 00:47:40.710 align:middle line:10%
is something called forgiveness.

00:47:40.710 --> 00:47:45.150 align:middle line:10%
And even when we take that word,
we take the word for giving.

00:47:45.150 --> 00:47:48.110 align:middle line:10%
It literally means for giving.

00:47:48.110 --> 00:47:51.900 align:middle line:84%
And many times when
we're hurt, we shut down.

00:47:51.900 --> 00:47:52.930 align:middle line:90%
We contract.

00:47:52.930 --> 00:47:54.897 align:middle line:84%
We pull back and we
don't give anymore.

00:47:54.897 --> 00:47:55.480 align:middle line:90%
We don't give.

00:47:55.480 --> 00:47:59.080 align:middle line:84%
If somebody hurts us, we don't
want to give them anything

00:47:59.080 --> 00:47:59.580 align:middle line:90%
anymore.

00:47:59.580 --> 00:48:01.440 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to
love them anymore.

00:48:01.440 --> 00:48:04.600 align:middle line:10%
>>Where somebody did
something terrible to us,

00:48:04.600 --> 00:48:08.160 align:middle line:10%
and now I am a better
person than they

00:48:08.160 --> 00:48:09.910 align:middle line:10%
are, because of what they did.

00:48:09.910 --> 00:48:13.410 align:middle line:84%
And now, you can
see how great I am,

00:48:13.410 --> 00:48:17.780 align:middle line:84%
or you can see how sad
I am, or how my life is.

00:48:17.780 --> 00:48:21.830 align:middle line:84%
And the issue around forgiveness
that people don't understand

00:48:21.830 --> 00:48:25.760 align:middle line:84%
is that when you
forgive, you have

00:48:25.760 --> 00:48:29.870 align:middle line:84%
to let go of the
personality you created.

00:48:29.870 --> 00:48:33.410 align:middle line:84%
>>Now imagine loving that
image inside your mind.

00:48:33.410 --> 00:48:35.810 align:middle line:84%
That's a choice that you
could make right now.

00:48:35.810 --> 00:48:38.760 align:middle line:84%
You could love your mate, your
partner, your dog, anybody

00:48:38.760 --> 00:48:41.920 align:middle line:84%
who you've ever thought to be
hurt or angry about, you could,

00:48:41.920 --> 00:48:45.640 align:middle line:84%
right now, inside your own
mind, bring up that image

00:48:45.640 --> 00:48:48.880 align:middle line:84%
and make a choice
to love that person

00:48:48.880 --> 00:48:50.500 align:middle line:90%
or that thing or that place.

00:48:50.500 --> 00:48:55.630 align:middle line:84%
And that changes not only the
dynamics of the way you think,

00:48:55.630 --> 00:48:59.290 align:middle line:84%
but the way you feel, the
way you perceive life.

00:48:59.290 --> 00:49:03.210 align:middle line:84%
The way you experience
life is really that simple.

00:49:03.210 --> 00:49:04.380 align:middle line:90%
It's a thought.

00:49:04.380 --> 00:49:08.946 align:middle line:84%
>>When I forgive, I
let go of the past.

00:49:08.946 --> 00:49:11.030 align:middle line:84%
And when I let go
of the past, there's

00:49:11.030 --> 00:49:13.680 align:middle line:90%
no thing there, nothing.

00:49:13.680 --> 00:49:16.830 align:middle line:84%
So in the space of
nothing, all is possible.

00:49:16.830 --> 00:49:19.560 align:middle line:84%
This is the space in
which alchemy happens.

00:49:19.560 --> 00:49:21.670 align:middle line:84%
This is the place in
which magic happens.

00:49:21.670 --> 00:49:24.460 align:middle line:84%
This is the place in
which creation happens.

00:49:24.460 --> 00:49:27.470 align:middle line:84%
But you can't get to
magic and creation

00:49:27.470 --> 00:49:31.180 align:middle line:84%
without forgiveness,
forgiveness of yourself,

00:49:31.180 --> 00:49:32.480 align:middle line:90%
forgiveness of others.

00:49:32.480 --> 00:49:39.800 align:middle line:84%
And a great example from my life
was that my stepfather ran off

00:49:39.800 --> 00:49:44.320 align:middle line:84%
with the marriage counselor
that he and my mother

00:49:44.320 --> 00:49:48.950 align:middle line:84%
were seeing because of his
affairs with other women.

00:49:48.950 --> 00:49:54.120 align:middle line:84%
And then had an affair with the
marriage counselor and left.

00:49:54.120 --> 00:49:56.530 align:middle line:90%
Then the house burnt down.

00:49:56.530 --> 00:49:58.830 align:middle line:90%
Then my mother died.

00:49:58.830 --> 00:50:01.040 align:middle line:84%
And then he married
the marriage counselor

00:50:01.040 --> 00:50:04.530 align:middle line:84%
and moved back onto
my mother's property.

00:50:04.530 --> 00:50:06.255 align:middle line:90%
I found this unforgivable.

00:50:06.255 --> 00:50:09.300 align:middle line:90%


00:50:09.300 --> 00:50:11.430 align:middle line:90%
Like unforgivable.

00:50:11.430 --> 00:50:15.250 align:middle line:84%
I even told him to be ready
for when I was old enough

00:50:15.250 --> 00:50:19.080 align:middle line:84%
to come back and take
care of business, i.e.,

00:50:19.080 --> 00:50:21.890 align:middle line:84%
he experienced that I
threatened his life,

00:50:21.890 --> 00:50:26.570 align:middle line:84%
and he put a order of protection
against me with the police

00:50:26.570 --> 00:50:30.840 align:middle line:84%
because he believed I was
going to come back to kill him.

00:50:30.840 --> 00:50:35.900 align:middle line:84%
And as a young man, I had so
much anger and so much rage

00:50:35.900 --> 00:50:40.890 align:middle line:84%
towards this other man who
I perceived had destroyed

00:50:40.890 --> 00:50:45.360 align:middle line:84%
my mother, and my
life, and my sister's.

00:50:45.360 --> 00:50:49.250 align:middle line:84%
And for many years I carried
this anger in my heart

00:50:49.250 --> 00:50:52.080 align:middle line:84%
that one day I would
become strong enough,

00:50:52.080 --> 00:50:54.660 align:middle line:84%
and smart enough,
and powerful enough

00:50:54.660 --> 00:50:58.940 align:middle line:90%
to go back and take care of him.

00:50:58.940 --> 00:51:02.080 align:middle line:84%
I perceived myself as this
young knight thrust out

00:51:02.080 --> 00:51:02.880 align:middle line:90%
into the world.

00:51:02.880 --> 00:51:05.060 align:middle line:84%
The King ran off
with the evil witch,

00:51:05.060 --> 00:51:06.970 align:middle line:84%
and the castle
burned to the ground,

00:51:06.970 --> 00:51:10.860 align:middle line:84%
and now I was a pauper,
alone in the world.

00:51:10.860 --> 00:51:16.820 align:middle line:84%
So in finding my
forgiveness for him,

00:51:16.820 --> 00:51:20.330 align:middle line:84%
what I realized when I
finally found him and was

00:51:20.330 --> 00:51:24.590 align:middle line:84%
able to talk to him is that
I said, here's the truth.

00:51:24.590 --> 00:51:27.690 align:middle line:84%
The truth was is I
loved you so much

00:51:27.690 --> 00:51:32.320 align:middle line:84%
and my heart was so
broken when you left.

00:51:32.320 --> 00:51:36.560 align:middle line:84%
And my mother's
heart was so broken,

00:51:36.560 --> 00:51:41.380 align:middle line:84%
and it was broken because
we loved you so much.

00:51:41.380 --> 00:51:44.680 align:middle line:84%
And I turned that
love into anger.

00:51:44.680 --> 00:51:52.820 align:middle line:84%
And I realized now that you
weren't trying to hurt us.

00:51:52.820 --> 00:51:56.460 align:middle line:84%
Your life was just happening
the way it happened.

00:51:56.460 --> 00:51:59.950 align:middle line:84%
There was not intent
to do me harm.

00:51:59.950 --> 00:52:03.980 align:middle line:84%
And so I want you to know
that though I don't condone

00:52:03.980 --> 00:52:07.400 align:middle line:84%
those actions, I don't
like the actions you took,

00:52:07.400 --> 00:52:11.890 align:middle line:84%
I truly have found
forgiveness for you.

00:52:11.890 --> 00:52:15.980 align:middle line:84%
And I'm asking you to
forgive me for having

00:52:15.980 --> 00:52:20.870 align:middle line:84%
made you the enemy for so
long and put so much anger

00:52:20.870 --> 00:52:23.760 align:middle line:90%
and separation between us.

00:52:23.760 --> 00:52:26.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Sometimes we think it's that
person that I should forgive

00:52:26.700 --> 00:52:28.960 align:middle line:90%
or that I need to forgive.

00:52:28.960 --> 00:52:32.290 align:middle line:84%
And at the deepest level,
it's really self forgiveness.

00:52:32.290 --> 00:52:34.470 align:middle line:90%
I would say that's the core.

00:52:34.470 --> 00:52:37.670 align:middle line:84%
It's forgiving ourselves
for all the things that we

00:52:37.670 --> 00:52:40.005 align:middle line:84%
may have thought that
we did or didn't do,

00:52:40.005 --> 00:52:42.430 align:middle line:84%
or all the things that we may
have thought that we've said

00:52:42.430 --> 00:52:43.930 align:middle line:90%
or didn't say.

00:52:43.930 --> 00:52:46.620 align:middle line:84%
What's interesting is as you
step back in life far enough,

00:52:46.620 --> 00:52:51.080 align:middle line:84%
you realize that we've
all been that person who

00:52:51.080 --> 00:52:54.620 align:middle line:84%
was on the other side of
the equation at some point.

00:52:54.620 --> 00:52:59.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Being unwilling to
forgive everything,

00:52:59.340 --> 00:53:05.270 align:middle line:84%
and mostly yourself, is just
another way of not being

00:53:05.270 --> 00:53:07.800 align:middle line:90%
responsible for your own life.

00:53:07.800 --> 00:53:12.030 align:middle line:90%


00:53:12.030 --> 00:53:14.050 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean if
everything is energy,

00:53:14.050 --> 00:53:16.510 align:middle line:84%
not forgiving
keeps energy stuck.

00:53:16.510 --> 00:53:22.580 align:middle line:90%


00:53:22.580 --> 00:53:24.695 align:middle line:84%
>> NARRATOR: So forgiving
is truly important.

00:53:24.695 --> 00:53:27.780 align:middle line:90%


00:53:27.780 --> 00:53:30.570 align:middle line:84%
But what if I'm still
struggling with stuck energy

00:53:30.570 --> 00:53:34.590 align:middle line:90%
like anger, blame, or judgment?

00:53:34.590 --> 00:53:39.070 align:middle line:84%
Later on my journey I met Gary
Renard, a teacher of a course

00:53:39.070 --> 00:53:44.670 align:middle line:84%
in miracles, and he taught me
a meditation tool that helps.

00:53:44.670 --> 00:53:50.770 align:middle line:84%
If you feel like,
feel free to share it.

00:53:50.770 --> 00:53:56.219 align:middle line:90%
Take a deep breath in and out.

00:53:56.219 --> 00:53:59.750 align:middle line:84%
Now, close your
eyes and visualize

00:53:59.750 --> 00:54:03.940 align:middle line:84%
the person you project on
in front of your inner eye.

00:54:03.940 --> 00:54:09.890 align:middle line:84%
Look at him and see that
he or she is only also

00:54:09.890 --> 00:54:11.399 align:middle line:90%
longing for love.

00:54:11.399 --> 00:54:22.430 align:middle line:90%


00:54:22.430 --> 00:54:30.060 align:middle line:90%
Now, you say to him or her,

00:54:30.060 --> 00:55:06.150 align:middle line:90%


00:55:06.150 --> 00:55:11.090 align:middle line:84%
This peace, unfortunately
didn't last very long.

00:55:11.090 --> 00:55:15.409 align:middle line:84%
Thoughts came crowding
back, the doubts, memories,

00:55:15.409 --> 00:55:16.450 align:middle line:90%
the whole merry-go-round.

00:55:16.450 --> 00:55:20.250 align:middle line:90%


00:55:20.250 --> 00:55:23.570 align:middle line:84%
>> Most people in their
minds are relating everything

00:55:23.570 --> 00:55:27.750 align:middle line:84%
to the past or they're
looking to the future.

00:55:27.750 --> 00:55:30.120 align:middle line:84%
Everything that they
do in the present

00:55:30.120 --> 00:55:33.170 align:middle line:84%
is a mixture of what
happened in the past

00:55:33.170 --> 00:55:37.016 align:middle line:84%
and what they want to
create in the future.

00:55:37.016 --> 00:55:40.720 align:middle line:84%
>> NARRATOR: There is a name
for it, the monkey mind.

00:55:40.720 --> 00:55:43.660 align:middle line:84%
The endless chattering
in our heads.

00:55:43.660 --> 00:55:45.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Thoughts cannot
bring you to peace.

00:55:45.730 --> 00:55:47.892 align:middle line:84%
Thoughts will bring
you to more thoughts.

00:55:47.892 --> 00:55:50.350 align:middle line:84%
They'll introduce their cousins
and their cousin's children

00:55:50.350 --> 00:55:52.100 align:middle line:84%
and everything, and
then your next minute,

00:55:52.100 --> 00:55:53.960 align:middle line:84%
you have a whole
family of thoughts

00:55:53.960 --> 00:55:56.990 align:middle line:90%
that you have to take care of.

00:55:56.990 --> 00:55:59.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Scientists who've done some
research on this believe that

00:55:59.920 --> 00:56:05.410 align:middle line:84%
each of us talks about 400
words per minute to ourself.

00:56:05.410 --> 00:56:08.790 align:middle line:84%
And these are constantly
judging our environment,

00:56:08.790 --> 00:56:11.150 align:middle line:84%
they're assessing our
situation, they're

00:56:11.150 --> 00:56:13.790 align:middle line:84%
giving us strategies on
how to deal with people,

00:56:13.790 --> 00:56:16.000 align:middle line:84%
how to look, how to
act, how to feel.

00:56:16.000 --> 00:56:17.790 align:middle line:84%
These are all coming
from inside of us,

00:56:17.790 --> 00:56:21.060 align:middle line:84%
and most people are actually
running on automatic pilot.

00:56:21.060 --> 00:56:24.970 align:middle line:84%
>> A simple analogy is
that if I am driving my car

00:56:24.970 --> 00:56:28.670 align:middle line:84%
on the freeway of my life
but all I am doing is looking

00:56:28.670 --> 00:56:30.520 align:middle line:84%
in the rear view
mirror the whole time,

00:56:30.520 --> 00:56:32.900 align:middle line:90%
I am guaranteed to crash.

00:56:32.900 --> 00:56:37.690 align:middle line:84%
>> This machine of thinking,
thinking, thinking, of wanting,

00:56:37.690 --> 00:56:40.200 align:middle line:84%
of intending, of
attracting and manifesting,

00:56:40.200 --> 00:56:46.440 align:middle line:84%
this machine is something
you could be aware.

00:56:46.440 --> 00:56:49.270 align:middle line:84%
It's like a parrot on your
shoulder all the time telling,

00:56:49.270 --> 00:56:50.765 align:middle line:84%
oh, you should have more,
you should have more,

00:56:50.765 --> 00:56:52.360 align:middle line:84%
you should have better,
you should get more,

00:56:52.360 --> 00:56:54.568 align:middle line:84%
you should be more rich,
you should be more powerful.

00:56:54.568 --> 00:56:56.390 align:middle line:84%
It's all the time
saying these things,

00:56:56.390 --> 00:56:58.060 align:middle line:90%
and it drives you through life.

00:56:58.060 --> 00:57:00.640 align:middle line:90%


00:57:00.640 --> 00:57:02.840 align:middle line:90%
You can't switch it off.

00:57:02.840 --> 00:57:04.080 align:middle line:90%
It's biological.

00:57:04.080 --> 00:57:04.821 align:middle line:90%
It's genetic.

00:57:04.821 --> 00:57:05.445 align:middle line:90%
It's automatic.

00:57:05.445 --> 00:57:08.340 align:middle line:90%
You can't switch it off.

00:57:08.340 --> 00:57:11.410 align:middle line:84%
But in the moment
that you can observe

00:57:11.410 --> 00:57:15.260 align:middle line:84%
the activities of
thought as automatic,

00:57:15.260 --> 00:57:18.360 align:middle line:90%
something interesting happens.

00:57:18.360 --> 00:57:23.900 align:middle line:84%
You become now, that, which
is aware of the thoughts.

00:57:23.900 --> 00:57:27.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, the thoughts are there
wanting, creating, manifesting,

00:57:27.970 --> 00:57:30.060 align:middle line:90%
attracting, intending.

00:57:30.060 --> 00:57:32.720 align:middle line:84%
The thoughts are
